<br>
Hrm, being a fan of the series, not a hardcore zealot, I found:<br>
<br>
The world is big, however, it's mostly full of water, you could cram the islands into a quarter of the map and save yerself a lot of sailing.<br>
<br>
Speaking of sailing, until you get the cyclone tune, expect to do a lot of it, especially if you are an avid explorer who likes to explore first, quest later.<br>
<br>
Maps, ugh, the word fuckmitten would spring to mind if I met the creator of the &quot;bait the fish thing in every single frikkin map square to get it labelled&quot; <br>
<br>
I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>hate</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the fish thing.<br>
<br>
The actual dungeons are better than Zelda 64's, no water dungeon here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Lotsa neat items n quests, just doesn't last long enough. ( I hear they cut two dungeons due to time constraints.)<br>
<br>
I had no preconceptions about the game, but it left me feeling kinda disappointed, rather like Metroid Prime...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :| --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/indifferent.gif ALT=":|"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2522<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/25/03 2:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1588.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Hmm, I'd have to say ..</span><hr size=1> .. Wasteland.  Then Fallout (just the first one).  After that, in no particular order, Eye of the Beholder, Various rogue-likes (UltraRogue, Hack (the original), Moria, Omega), Magic Candle, Might and Magic I, Wing Commander I.  Falcon.<br>
